projects.name: DESIGNED A FRONTEND FOR TRAFFIC LIGHTS
MINI PROJECT ACCIDENT PREVENTION IN HILL STATIONS
projects.description: According to a report, 10% of all car collisions in hill stations occur on curving roadways. Driving through curves and bends is dangerous. An IoT-based Accident Prevention System for Hairpin Bend Roads has been offered in this work as a potential option. The answer of this problem is alerting the motive force about the vehicle coming from opposite side. This is often done by keeping the ultrasonic sensor in one side of the road before the curve and keeping a LED light after the curve, so that vehicle comes from one side of curve a senses and LED light glow at opposite side. By viewing the LED light green and red criteria the motive force can become alert and may hamper the speed of vehicle.

projects.name: MAJOR PROJECT VEHICLES AUTO KIDS RECOGINTION SYSTEM
projects.description: Recently many cases have been reported of children left behind or forgotten in locked vehices due to unforeseen circumstances such forgetfulness, distractions, stress, and nervousness. In this study an intelligent recognition system for detecting kids present in vehicles has been developed as an important safety system. The system is used to detectthe present of a child in locked cars and put forward both a warning and procedural protocolfor child safety.
